+# po-formulas-retro
+
+Sibling formula pack for [`prefect-orchestration`][po]. Closes the
+feedback loop on PO runs: collects recent `lessons-learned.md` +
+`decision-log.md` artifacts from a target pack's run dirs, asks
+Claude to identify **recurring** patterns (≥3 distinct runs), and
+commits proposed prompt / skill / CLAUDE.md edits back to the
+target pack's repo.
+
+Single-occurrence lessons land in `bd remember "[<target_pack>] ..."`
+rather than file edits — see `skills/retro/SKILL.md` for the full
+boundaries.
+
+[po]: https://github.com/nanocorps/prefect-orchestration
+
+## Install (editable, for development)
+
+```bash
+po install --editable ../prefect-orchestration
+po install --editable .
+po update      # refresh entry-point metadata
+po list        # confirm `update-prompts-from-lessons` is listed
+```
+
+## Run
+
+```bash
+po run update-prompts-from-lessons \
+    --target-pack po-formulas-software-dev \
+    --rig-path /abs/path/to/rig \
+    --since 7d
+```
+
+`--dry-run true` writes the summary artifact under
+`<rig-path>/.planning/update-prompts-from-lessons/<utc-ts>/` but does
+not edit files, commit, or call `bd remember`.
+
+## Deploy (weekly cron)
+
+```bash
+po deploy --apply        # applies the `retro-weekly` deployment to your Prefect server
+prefect deployment run \
+    update-prompts-from-lessons/retro-weekly \
+    --param target_pack=po-formulas-software-dev \
+    --param rig_path=/abs/path/to/rig
+```
+
+The deployment uses the `po` work pool (Cron `0 9 * * 0`, UTC).
+
+## Tests
+
+```bash
+uv run python -m pytest tests/
+```
