@@ -0,0 +1,70 @@
+# Retro skill — boundaries
+
+The `update-prompts-from-lessons` formula closes the feedback loop on
+PO runs. It walks recent `lessons-learned.md` and `decision-log.md`
+artifacts, asks Claude to identify recurring patterns (≥3 distinct
+runs), and proposes edits to the target pack's prompts / skills /
+top-level guidance.
+
+## What the retro MAY change
+
+- `agents/<role>/prompt.md` (and any nested `**/agents/<role>/prompt.md`)
+- `skills/<name>/SKILL.md` (and any nested `**/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`)
+- `CLAUDE.md` (top-level or nested)
+
+## What the retro MUST NOT change
+
+- **NOT code** (`*.py`, anything under `po_formulas_retro/`, or the
+  target pack's modules). Lessons about code go into prompts; agents
+  read prompts every run, so prompt edits are the durable artifact.
+- `pyproject.toml` (no dependency or entry-point churn from a retro)
+- Tests (`tests/**`)
+- CI / workflow YAML (`.github/**`, `.gitlab-ci.yml`, etc.)
+
+The orchestrator double-checks every proposed `target_file` against an
+allow-list (`is_allowed_target_path`) and silently drops anything else.
+A creative synthesizer cannot trick the flow into editing code.
+
+## Recurrence bar
+
+A theme must show up in **3+ distinct run dirs** (different `id`
+attributes) before it qualifies for a file edit. Single-occurrence
+observations are recorded via `bd remember "[<target_pack>] <note>"`
+instead — that keeps prompts grep-able and prevents bloat from one-off
+incidents.
+
+`bd` does not natively support per-pack memory tagging; the
+`[<target_pack>]` prefix is the convention until it does. Search with
+`bd memories <pack-name>`.
+
+## Branch + commit policy
+
+- If the target repo's current branch is `main` or `master`, the flow
+  cuts a fresh `retro/<utc-ts>` branch (collisions resolve via
+  `-1`, `-2`, ...).
+- Otherwise the commit lands on the active feature branch.
+- Commit message: `retro(<target_pack>): integrate lessons from <N> runs since <since>`.
+- `git add` is **scoped** — only the files the synthesizer proposed.
+  Never `git add -A` (CLAUDE.md polyrepo rule).
+- Commit hooks are bypassed (`-c core.hooksPath=/dev/null`) so a
+  pre-commit hook on the target repo can't auto-push the retro commit.
+- The flow **never** pushes. Humans review the branch, rebase, merge.
+
+## Refusal conditions
+
+The flow refuses (returns `{"refused": ...}`, makes no commits, no
+`bd remember` calls) when:
+
+- the target pack is not installed
+- the target pack's distribution metadata says it isn't editable
+  (`direct_url.json` missing or `dir_info.editable != True`)
+- the resolved source path has no `.git` ancestor (monorepo packs
+  installed from a subdir without a git root, or unusual layouts)
+
+## When NOT to run a retro
+
+- Fewer than ~10 runs in the time window — the recurrence bar can't
+  bite, almost everything will be `single_occurrence`. Bump `--since`
+  or skip the run.
+- Mid-merge on the target repo — wait until the working tree is clean
+  so your retro commit doesn't entangle with in-flight work.
